description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen within the Medicine Directorate for a Medical PA with waiting list experience to join an established team within the Cardiac Surgery Department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate must have proven secretarial/personal assistant experience. You will be responsible for supporting the clinical team, managing diaries, clinical commitments, waiting lists and annual leave. You will use your judgement skills to prioritise tasks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for adding/removing patients to the NUH waiting list and co-ordinating/booking admission to hospital, using hospital IT systems, e.g. Medway PAS/Bluespier. You must have a good understanding of current NHS targets including 18 week Referral to Treatment. You will need to be able to demonstrate a clear understanding of confidentiality issues, be well motivated and reliable. You must be able to forward think and problem solve.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are an enthusiastic and conscientious team player with excellent time management and organisational skills. You are an effective communicator and you must be able to demonstrate behaviours consistent with the Trust&#39;s &#39;We Are Here for You&#39; behavioural standards. It is essential to have excellent audio typing skills, knowledge of medical terminology and previous recent experience in a secretarial role. Waiting list experience is desirable. You are adaptable and flexible in your approach to work and committed to providing a first class service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
